<sect>Introduktion

<p>
<bf/KDE Ikon Editoren/ er designet til at hjælpe med at lave ikoner til KDE desktoppen ved
brug af KDE ikon paletten.

<p>
Jeg håber du finder programmet brugbart og jeg vil sætte pris på forslag og kommentarer.
<p>
<tt/Thomas Tanghus/
<htmlurl url="mailto:tanghus@earthling.net" name="tanghus@earthling.net">.
<p>

<sect>Installation
<p>

<sect1>Hvor finder jeg Ikon Editoren
<p>
<bf/KDE Ikon Editoren/ kan findes på <url
url="ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/unstable/apps/graphics">, KDE projektets primære site eller på
<htmlurl url="http://w1.1358.telia.com/~u135800018" name="min hjemmeside">.

<sect1>Systemkrav
<p>
For succesfuldt at kunne kompilere ikon editoren, har du brug for enten kdelibs-1.0 eller
de nyeste versioner af <tt> libkdecore</tt>, <tt> libkdeui</tt>, <tt> libkfile</tt> og <tt> libkfm</tt>.
Alle krævede libraries så vel som KDE Ikon Editoren selv kan findes på <url
url="ftp://ftp.kde.org/pub/kde/">.

<sect1>Kompilering og installering
<p>
For at kompilere og installere <bf/KDE Ikon Editoren/ på dit system, tast følgende
i det directory hvor du har udpakket Ikon Editor distributionen:
<tscreen>
<verb> 
% ./configure 
% make 
% make install 
</verb>
</tscreen>

Da Ikon Editoren bruger <tt/autoconf/ og <tt/automake/ skulle du ikke få problemer
med at kompilere den. Skulle det alligevel volde problemer så rapporter det venligst
til <bf/KDE/ mailing listen.

<sect1>Konfiguration
<p>

<sect>Onscreen Fundamentals
<p>
In this section will be briefly described the Icon Editor user interface. 
<p>
The Icon Editor window is separated in four areas: main toolbar, tools toolbar
grid and statusbar.
<p>

<sect1>Main toolbar
<p>
<descrip>
	<tag/New File/
	Create a new ikon. If the current file has been modified you will be asked if you
	want to save the changes. After that a dialog will open where you can choose to create
	the ikon from scratch or from a template (templates requires kdelibs > 1.0).
	<tag/Open/ 
	Open an existing icon file.
	<p>
	<tag/Save/
	Save the currently open icon.
	<p>
	<tag/Print/
	Print the icon
	<tag/Cut/
	Cuts out the entire icon and put it onto the clipboard.
	<p>
	<tag/Copy/
	Copies the entire icon to the clipboard.
	<p>
	<tag/Paste/
	Paste the contents of the clipboard as a new image (if the clipboard contains a valid icon).
	<p>
	<tag/Resize/
	Resize icon to width X height (req. kdelibs > 1.0)
	<p>
	<tag/Gray scale/
	Gray scale the icon image. This may create colors not conformant to the KDE icon palette.
	<p>
	<tag/Zoom in/
	<p>
	<tag/Zoom out/
	<p>
	<tag/Zoom factor/
	Zoom to predefined zoom factor.
	<p>
	<tag/Toggle grid/
	Toggle grid on/off.
	<p>
	<tag/New Icon Editor/
	Open a new Icon Editor window.
	<p>

</descrip>

<sect1>Tools toolbar
<p>
This toolbar contains the tools you can use to manipulate the icon.
<descrip>
	<tag/Find color/
	Doesn't change the icon but changes the current drawcolor to the color clicked on.
	<p>
	<tag/Freehand/
	Draw free hand.
	<p>
	<tag/Select/
	Select (mark) a part of the icon.
	<p>
	<tag/Line/
	Draw a line.
	<p>
	<tag/Rectangle/
	Draw a rectangle.
	<p>
	<tag/Filled rectangle/
	Draw a filled rectangle.
	<p>
	<tag/Circle/
	Draw a circle.
	<p>
	<tag/Filled circle/
	Draw a filled circle.
	<p>
	<tag/Ellipse/
	<p>
	<tag/Filled ellipse/
	Almost the same as drawing a circle.
	<p>
	<tag/Spray/
	Draws a randow dotted pattern like a spraycan.
	<p>
	<tag/Flood fill/
	Fill an area with the current color..
	<p>
	<tag/Eraser/
	Draw transparent (invisible).
</descrip>


<sect1>Grid
<p>
The grid is where you manipulate the icon contents.
<sect1>Statusbar

<sect>The Menu Entries
<p>

<sect1>File
<p>
The following functions are available from the file menu:
<descrip>
	<tag/New Window/
	Open a new Icon Editor window.
	<p>
	<tag/New .../
	Lets you create a new Icon either from a <bf/template/ or by specifying the size.
	<p>
	<tag/Open/ 
	Open an existing icon file.
	<p>
	<tag/Save/
	Save the currently open icon.
	<p>
	<tag/Save as/
	Save the currently open icon under a new name.
	<p>
	<tag/Print/
	Print the icon
	<p>
	<tag/Close/
	Close the icon Editor window.
	<p>
	<tag/Exit/
	Close all Icon Editor windows opened ( by this instance ),
</descrip>


<sect1>Edit
<p>
The Edit menu contains the following entries:
<descrip>
	<tag/Cut/
	Cuts out the entire icon and put it onto the clipboard.
	<p>
	<tag/Copy/
